==English==

{{rank|longer|paid|art|478|neither|suddenly|act|la}}

===[[Determiner]]===<!-- or perhaps a quantifier, or both -->
'''neither'''

# not [[one]] nor the [[other]]; not [[either]]
#* '''neither''' definition seems correct

===Pronoun===
'''neither'''

# not either one
#* because '''neither''' is correct

===Translations===
*German: [[keine]]

===Conjunction===
'''neither'''

# not either (used with [[nor]])
#* '''neither''' I nor you like it
# also not
#* if you won’t correct it, '''neither''' will I

===Adverb===
'''neither'''

# similarly not
#* just as you would not correct it, neither would I

===Usage notes===
'''Neither''' is traditionally used to mean none of two.  Use [[none]] with more than two things.

